cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about building a comprehensive corpus for Chinese clinical texts with syntactic and semantic annotations, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers research on NLP and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning methods for annotation and quality assurance, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Information retrieval (cs.IR) could also be relevant as the paper discusses the development of a Chinese clinical text processing and information extraction system. Finally, the paper involves the study of Chinese texts in the clinical domain, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the application of NLP techniques to a specific domain.
